# ── Server-side secrets (set in Netlify UI → Site settings → Environment variables) ──
# Visual Crossing key, used by netlify/functions/weather.mts. NEVER commit the real key.
# Get one free at https://www.visualcrossing.com/weather-api/
# VISUALCROSSING_API_KEY=your-visualcrossing-key

# ── Client-side config (VITE_ vars are PUBLIC — bundled into the JS) ──

# OpenTripMap API key (free tier) — "Top things to do nearby" on destination pages.
VITE_OPENTRIPMAP_API_KEY=your-opentripmap-key

# Local dev only: lets `vite dev` call Visual Crossing directly without `netlify dev`.
# Use a throwaway key — anything in VITE_ is visible to users. Leave unset in production.
# VITE_VISUALCROSSING_API_KEY=your-dev-visualcrossing-key
